{
  "texts": [
    "Instead, it is based on statistical laws and most RALMs accomplish this task based on rules.",
    "The Selfmem (Cheng et al., 2024) system employs two distinct language models for the machine translation task.",
    "The first is a trainable mini-model, which has been trained using a joint and bipartite approach, respectively.",
    "The second is a few-shot prompted LLM.",
    "Ultimately, Selfmem has demonstrated a notable enhancement in its performance across all four translation directions and for both training architectures."
  ]
}